ard, and there was no significant difference in errors collectively\namongst all methods tested. In addition, there were no significant differences\nbetween existing and MR-less tau PET quantification methods. We conclude that a\ntemplate-based method is a feasible alternative to, or salvage for, direct\nregistration and MR-less quantification; and, may be preferred in cases where\nthere is doubt about the similarity between two image modalities.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 15 Oct 2020 17:21:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-16"}
