c calculation that described the unique properties of the $0^+_1\\to\n4^+_1$ transition. In the inelastic scattering to the $4^+_1$ state, the\ndominant two-step process of the $0^+_1\\to 2^+_1\\to 4^+_1$ transitions and the\ndeconstructive interference is the weak one-step process were essential.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 16 Oct 2020 04:08:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-19"}
