{"id":"2010.08294","submitter":"Mathieu Ballandras","authors":"Mathieu Ballandras","title":"Trivializations of moment maps","comments":"Clarification of historical facts","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.RT math.DG","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We study various trivializations of moment maps. First in the general\nframework of a reductive group $G$ acting on a smooth affine variety. We prove\nthat the moment map is a locally trivial fibration over a regular locus of the\ncenter of the Lie algebra of $H$ a maximal compact subgroup of $G$. The\nconstruction relies on Kempf-Ness theory and Morse theory of the square norm of\nthe moment map studied by Kirwan, Ness-Mumford and Sjamaar. Then we apply it\ntogether with ideas from Nakajima and Kronheimer to trivialize the hyperkaehler\nmoment map for Nakajima quiver varieties. Notice this trivialization result\nabout quiver varieties was known and used by experts such as Nakajima and\nMaffei but we could not locate a proof in the literature.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 16 Oct 2020 10:35:38 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 6 Nov 2020 14:15:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-11-09"}
